title: 3 U.S. troops were killed and 25 wounded in a drone strike on a base in Jordan
description: The White House says Iran-backed militant groups are behind the attack. It comes amid the conflict in the Middle East that the U.S. has been working to keep from spreading through the region.

title: Gaza puppeteer doesn't let the war stop his passion
description: Yousef al-Hindi, a puppeteer from Gaza, continues his passion despite the war between Israel and Hamas by using whatever materials he can find.

title: House GOP releases impeachment articles in bid to oust Homeland Security's Mayorkas
description: Republicans contend Mayorkas' "willful and systemic refusal to comply with the law" on immigration amounts to "high crimes and misdemeanors" for failing to manage the U.S.-Mexico border.

title: Climate activists throw soup at glass protecting Mona Lisa in Paris
description: Two climate activists hurled soup Sunday at the glass protecting the Mona Lisa at the Louvre Museum in Paris and shouted slogans advocating for a sustainable food system.

title: Greyhound stations were once a big part of America. Now, many of them are being shut
description: Greyhound bus stations are being shut down and redeveloped. The closures are leaving passengers without a warm place to get a snack, use the restroom or wait for the bus.

title: What to know about the NFL conference championship games
description: The victors of Sunday's games will face each another in the Super Bowl. It's the Baltimore Ravens versus the Kansas City Chiefs and, later, the San Francisco 49ers against the Detroit Lions.

title: How a West Bank Palestinian theater went from symbol of hope to casualty of war
description: Jenin's Freedom Theatre was ransacked by Israeli soldiers, its staff thrown in jail. Once celebrated as a peace initiative, it's the latest casualty of near-daily military raids on the West Bank.

title: Nearly 25,000 tech workers were laid in the first weeks of 2024. What's going on?
description: Silicon Valley executives have said the cuts are a result of pandemic overhiring and still-historically-high inflation. But others say something else may be behind the mass layoffs.

title: Nearly 25,000 tech workers were laid off in the first weeks of 2024. Why is that?
description: Silicon Valley executives have said the cuts are a result of pandemic overhiring and still-historically-high inflation. But others say something else may be behind the mass layoffs.

title: The Pro Volleyball Federation for women debuts and draws a record crowd.
description: It's a new league and a new era for women's volleyball. The Pro Volleyball Federation held its first match in Nebraska.  The seven team league will add three more teams in 2025.

title: House Democratic candidates make abortion access top focus of '24 campaigns
description: Democrats are targeting seats with first-term GOP incumbents in states where access to abortion rights could resonate with swing voters.

title: Finns go to polls to elect new president, at unprecedented time for NATO newcomer
description: Voters in Finland were electing a new president Sunday at an unprecedented time for the Nordic nation that is now a NATO member with its eastern border with Russia closed.

title: Iran launches three satellites into space as tensions rise
description: Iran says it successfully launched three satellites into space with a rocket that had multiple failures in the past, the latest for a program that the West says improves Tehran's ballistic missiles.

title: Ukraine says corrupt officials stole $40 million meant to buy arms for the war
description: Employees from a Ukrainian arms firm conspired with defense ministry officials to embezzle almost $40 million earmarked to buy shells for the war with Russia, Ukraine's security service reported.
